ZH: 外面打雷了，很可能会下雨。
EN: It's thundering outside, it's likely going to rain.

ZH: 打雷的声音吓到了小狗。
EN: The sound of thunder scared the little dog.

ZH: 昨天晚上打雷了，把我吓了一跳。
EN: It thundered last night and gave me a fright.

ZH: 我不喜欢打雷，会让我感到害怕。
EN: I don't like thunder, it makes me feel scared.

ZH: 打雷的时候，我总是躲在被窝里。
EN: When it thunders, I always hide under the covers.

ZH: 不要害怕，只是在外面打雷而已。
EN: Don't be scared, it's just thundering outside.

ZH: 打雷的声音越来越大了。
EN: The thunder is getting louder.

ZH: 我从小就害怕打雷。
EN: I have been afraid of thunder since I was little.

ZH: 天气预报说今天会有雷雨，肯定会打雷的。
EN: The weather forecast says there will be thunderstorms today, for sure it will thunder.

ZH: 在这儿打雷的情况是经常发生的。
EN: Thunderstorms are common here.

ZH: 如果你害怕打雷，可以用耳塞来减轻声音。
EN: If you are afraid of thunder, you can use earplugs to reduce the sound.

ZH: 打雷的声音像是上帝在生气。
EN: The sound of thunder is like God being angry.

ZH: 老太太告诉小孩子，雷声是龙在哭泣。
EN: The old lady told the children that thunder is the sound of dragons crying.

ZH: 大雨伴随着打雷，令人感到恐惧。
EN: Heavy rain accompanied by thunder is scary.

ZH: 大自然的力量展示在打雷这一瞬间。
EN: The power of nature is displayed in the moment of thunder.

ZH: 打雷的时候最好不要躲在树下。
EN: It's best not to hide under trees when it's thundering.

ZH: 我在打雷的恐惧之中终于入睡了。
EN: I finally fell asleep in the fear of thunder.

ZH: 打雷的声音响彻整个山谷。
EN: The sound of thunder echoed through the entire valley.

ZH: 躲在屋里，听着打雷声，觉得很舒服。
EN: Hiding in the house, listening to the sound of thunder, feels very comforting.

ZH: 打雷的声音让巴士上的乘客们惊恐不已。
EN: The sound of thunder terrified the passengers on the bus.
